Product name: 26 in. SUNBURST WALL ART  2 tiered steel rod and brass welding 1970 vintage era
Description:
SUNNY SIDE UP 
The brutalist style or era , that was very popular in the 60s 70s come from the fact that the welding and torch cutting , where done in a ( brutal manners ) meaning the artist does his basic action on the moment and does not tamper with it after , leaving the art pieces raw . To perform that you need a steady hand , a good knowledge of what your doing and a zenlike attitude ! Just imagine missing one weld ... Next !
One of the most notable artists in this genre and the most sought after art pieces is from Curtis Jere .
The brutalism term is applicable to wood carving , sculptures , furnitures (Paul Evans), forteress like architecture (Le corbusier ) , always with the raw , rebelious , akward look behind them .
Our full sculptural 2 tiered sunburst is 26 inches in diameter , featuring  steel rods and brass welding ....... Ready to hang on your wall.

Description:

Product name: Hmong Hand Woven Indigo Hemp Fabric Vintage Soft Cool Hill Tribe Natural Organic
Description:
Length - By the yard
Width -  11" / 27cm
Weight - approx 2.30 oz / 75g per yard
BY THE YARD PRICE 7.50, please contact us for a custom order. Discount available for larger orders.
Genuine Hmong hand woven hemp. Light indigo colour. Soft, fine woven vintage re-claimed hemp.
The hemp is grown by the Hmong tribeswomen, dried, and the hemp fiber stripped from the stem and pounded, boiled, spun and coated with wax before it can be strung on an old wooden loom and woven into the finished product. All year around the tribeswomen can be seen with hemp fibers wound around their hands, using what spare time they have to connect the separate fibers to make one use-able thread.
The Indigo dye is obtained from a plant also grown by the tribe on the edge of their steep rice terraced mountainsides. The fresh cut hemp and the dye can bee seen in the last set of images.
We buy this fabric directly from a number of elderly Hmong women, in a small village, in Northern Vietnam. Vintage used hemp but recently dyed this light indigo colour.
We ship with the very efficient Vietnam Post Office, all orders are trackable, all shipping costs are exactly what VNpost charge us, no profit made on shipping, all shipping overcharges refunded.

Product name: City of Refuge, Hawaii Stamp – 11 Cent Air Mail Stamp– National Park Centennial Issue - Block of 4 Unused  Stamps- Vintage US Postage Stamps
Description:
These 11¢ City of Refuge airmail stamps are part of the National Park Centennial Issue of 1972.  They were issued on May 3, 1972.  This listing is for a block of 4 unused stamps.  
The stamp features a statue of Ki’i with the City of Refuge in the background.  All text is in black – “Natinal Parks Centennial” is along the left margin.  “City of Refuge – Hawaii” is underneath the picture;  “U.S. 11c Air Mail” is in the upper left corner.
Ki’i is an ancient Hawaiian god.  The City of Refuge served as a sanctuary for early Hawaiians that sought purification from temple priests after breaking a kapu (ancient law).  It also served as a place to escape from enemies.  The City of Refuge became a National Park in 1955 – its name was changed on 11/10/19 and again in 2000.  It is now known as Puuhonua O Honaunau National Historical Park.
Each stamp measures 1 3/4” x 1” (4.5 cm x 2.5 cm). The full block measures 3 1/4” x 2” tall (8.3 cm x 5.1 cm).
These stamps are “mint” – meaning they have never been used. They have the original glue.
My grand-aunt collected these. She was not a “true” stamp collector & basically stored them in manila envelopes. Whenever the USPS came out with a new stamp – especially a commemorative one – she purchased at least one sheet & put them away in her envelopes.  More stamps from her collection can be found here: 
https://www.etsy.com/shop/4GetMeNotTreasures/search?search_query=postagestamps
 or by browsing through the Stamps & Ephemera section of the shop here: 
https://www.etsy.com/shop/4GetMeNotTreasures?section_id=18798963.
  Holiday and Christmas stamps can be found by browsing through the Holiday Home section here: 
https://www.etsy.com/shop/4GetMeNotTreasures?section_id=10146857
 
These stamps are great for collectors both young and old alike. Additionally, they’d be great for paper crafting & jewelry making or anywhere else your creativity wants to take you. They are also a great gift for someone born on the day the stamps were issued. Frame them and give them as a nice and thoughtful gift – or keep them for yourself.
To go to the shop home page visit 
https://www.etsy.com/shop/4GetMeNotTreasures

Product name: GREYHOUND Dog Booties, Dog Shoes, Dog Boots
Description:
Protect your dog's paws with a set of K9 Apparel Booties. Outdoors, our Booties protect paws from road salt, snow, ice, and harsh lawn chemicals. Indoors, our booties provide stability for your dog when standing on wood or tile surfaces—also protecting wood floors from scratches. Warmth and comfort are built in the design of our slipper-style dog booties. Featuring a protective non-slip embossed Mega Grip bottom that is completely lined with soft, warm Polartec® polar fleece, our booties are uniquely designed with an extra-long upper portion and two sturdy bands of velcro to help hold the booties in place on your Greyhound. Available as a set of four black booties.
 - Polartec polar fleece is soft, comfortable, and warm. This quick-drying fabric is colorfast, does not pill, and is machine washable. Polartec® 200 Classic double velour fabric. Made in the USA.
 - Embossed Mega Grip is a durable rubberized fabric that works well on ice and in snow but wears out on concrete, asphalt, and abrasive surfaces.
Choose the bootie size according to your dog's weight.
Tip: Before you order dog booties, see if your dog is likely to accept them. 
Get two pairs of baby socks or kid's socks that fit your dog's paws. Put two of the socks on either the front or back paws and have your dog stand on a non-slippery surface. If your dog is okay wearing two socks, put socks on the remaining paws and allow some time for your dog to get used to the socks. If your dog will move around wearing all four socks, this is a good indication your dog will accept wearing booties. However, if your dog does not accept wearing socks, it is unlikely your dog will accept wearing booties and we suggest not purchasing booties for your dog.
Note: BOOTIES ARE NON RETURNABLE, NON REFUNDABLE AND NON EXCHANGEABLE.

Product name: Unique New Mom Gifts, Godson Baptism Gift, Gift From Aunt, For Goddaughter, Gift From Godmother, Godson Christening, Adoption Gifts
Description:
A Charming & Unique Handmade Baby Gift
Rudkin is a handsome, handmade needle felted bunny rabbit with a ginormous tail - and he is the hero of my self-penned rhyming child's storybook. You will receive Rudkin & the storybook nestled snugly in a small kraft box.
If you're new to the concept of needle felting, it is the art of creating felted objects out of unspun wool and fiber using a repeated jabbing action with barbed felting needles. The creations can be 3-dimensional or flat; fun or functional.
This rhyming story is designed to be read out to your little ones, who can see the story come to life as you act out the adventure with your little needle felt bunny.
The story is beautifully printed on 170gsm natural kraft card. The story is 18 pages in total and each page is approximately 3" x 3". It is bound together by small metal bindings. Rudkin has the initial 'R' hand sewn onto his badge. He is approx. 3" tall.
## Personalisation ##
1) I can print a personal message (up to 10 words) on the front cover... 
A birthday story for Emily 
A story to read aloud to Simon
2) I can also hand sew the initial of the child's first name on to the badge of your needle felt bunny (instead of the R) as an added personal touch.
Please message me the details with your order so we can ensure everything is correct.
## Shipping ##
Your item will travel to you Royal Mail 1st Class Signed For (UK) and Royal Mail International Tracked / Tracked & Signed (if your country provides this service) everywhere else. This service allows you to track your item along the way. 
Please note: Rudkin is needle-felted by hand using natural wool and some synthetic fibres. He is a miniature and is intended to be a collectors item as opposed to a toy. He is not mass-produced and has not been safety tested as a toy. Unsupervised play with Rudkin is not recommended.
The book is not safety tested and is not a toy. It is designed to be read aloud by a responsible adult and NOT designed to be left alone with children. This is due to small parts and bindings which hold the book together and could be swallowed if dismantled or detached.

Product name: 12 Little Spinning Tops, Unfinished Hardwood
Description:
Here is a very basic, simple top that will provide hours of fun for both children and adults!  These are unfinished hardwood so the fun starts with maybe some touch up sanding and the painting.  Solid color or swirls of color?  Polka dot or stripes?  What will it look like when it is spun??  And, if you are a really good spinner, what will it look like balanced on the end of your finger?  Ron used to spin one of these tops on the end of his finger at craft shows.  Always a show stopper!  The only trouble was, when other people tried that in the booth, we would have tops zinging in all directions!!  It does take a little practice.
The tops consist of a 1-1/2 inch in diameter by 1/2 inch thick disc and a 1-1/2 inch long by 1/4  hardwood dowel sharpened at one end.  Because of shipping/handling costs involved, we will only sell these in lots of 12 or more.  If you only want one or two (or anything less than twelve), you can add them to other items you are ordering at  .75 each, but we will not ship less than twelve by themselves.  Just convo us for a custom order of all the items you want with adjusted shipping on your combined order.
These tops could be a choking hazard for young children or pets that like to put things in their mouths.  The tops are not recommended for children under five for that reason and because of the sharp point on the end.  KNOW YOUR CHILD AND BUY ACCORDINGLY!
The tops will ship First Class Parcel in the USA and First Class International outside the USA.  If your country is not on our list, please contact us for shipping information.
*******************************************************
*******************************************************
PLEASE READ:  IMPORTANT SHIPPING INFORMATION!!
SHIPPING USA:  First Class Parcel pricing is by the ounce (up to 13 ounces)and is the SAME (by ounces) anywhere in the USA.  Priority Mail and Parcel Select rates change depending on weight, size, and distance.  Our pricing is based on rates to the West Coast since a majority of our sales are in that rate bracket.  If you live closer to Michigan, please ask for adjusted shipping rates BEFORE you send a purchase order and we will set up a Reserved Listing for you.  Just “convo” or e-mail us with your ZIP CODE and a list of the items you wish to purchase.  We will set up the Reserved Listing for you with the revised shipping and you can order as usual.  (Keep in mind that I cannot see what is in your shopping cart!)
Of course, you can always just order and pay and we will refund any shipping overpayment if it is above 2.00!  Our shipping refunds go through PayPal and are done at the same time as we print up your shipping label.  No long waits for a refund!
MULTIPLE ITEMS:   I’m afraid I got tired of trying to guess at shipping for multiple items when we have such a variety of items and weights.  It just doesn't work for us.  We do offer combined shipping; we just can't show it on the listing!  Please e-mail or convo me for shipping on multiple items BEFORE YOU CHECK OUT and we will be glad to give you a price on shipping to your door!  Shipping is usually much less for one combined shipping price than for the shipping prices on each item added together! Although, sometimes it is cheaper to ship in two First Class Parcels than in one Priority package when shipping to the West Coast!  Just another shipping nightmare to deal with.  See above paragraphs for more info.
USA SHIPPING TIMES:  First Class Parcel delivers in 2 to 5 business days. Priority Mail delivers in 2 to 3 business days.  Parcel Select delivers in 5 to 9 business days.  All have tracking included.  We do not ship Express Mail!  Insurance is additional.  If you would like insurance, please ask to have it added to your order BEFORE purchasing.
INTERNATIONAL ORDERS:  First Class International is by the ounce up to 4 pounds.  Priority International is by the pound and is used for anything over 4 pounds.  Rates are high, but we do the best we can.  We do combined shipping on multiple orders the same as we do in the USA.  Refunds are also treated the same.  Any duties, fees, taxes that might occur when your package passes through customs is your responsibility.  Every country handles small parcels a little differently. 
Currently, First Class takes from 6 to 15 business days (or more) with tracking available in a few countries.  Priority takes 6 to 10 business days with tracking and some insurance included.
**********************************************************
For additional information on shipping, insurance, payment options, return policies, combined orders, etc., go to SHOP POLICIES.  For more info about us, vintage, craft tips, and all kinds of odds and ends, go to our PROFILE!

Description:
Meet Rudkin! He is an adorable handmade needle felted bunny rabbit with a ginormous tail - and he is the hero of my self-penned rhyming child's storybook.
You will receive both Rudkin and the storybook nestled snugly in a small kraft box; it is a very cute gift for a toddler or new born baby and an ideal baby shower gift.

Most of the fleece I use to needle felt Rudkin is hand sheared from my own little flock of 5 ewes. They were all orphan lambs when I got them and I bottle fed each one giving them a wonderful start in life. If you're new to the concept of needle felting, it is the art of creating felted objects out of unspun wool and fiber using a repeated jabbing action with barbed felting needles. The creations can be 3-dimensional or flat; fun or functional.

A story to read aloud to Simon

Please message me the details with your order so we can ensure everything is correct.
## Shipping ##
Your item will travel to you Royal Mail 1st Class Signed For (UK) and Royal Mail International Tracked / Tracked & Signed (if your country provides this service) everywhere else. This service allows you to track your item along the way. 
## Please Note ##
Rudkin is needle-felted by hand using natural wool and some synthetic fibres. He is a miniature and is intended to be a collectors item as opposed to a toy. He is not mass-produced and has not been safety tested as a toy. Unsupervised play with Rudkin is not recommended.

Product name: Shut the Box game
Description:
This is our take on the classic pub game called 'Shut the Box'. The box is crafted from hickory, with walnut sliders, and is designed to be portable.
To play, the dice are rolled and any combination of number(s) which add up to the total on the dice, may be covered. A player continues rolling the dice until no additional numbers can be covered. At which point the game is over, and the uncovered numbers are added up for the final score. The goal is to get the lowest score possible. 
There is also a two player version where one player attempts to cover numbers and the other player tries to uncover numbers. The winner is the first one to cover / uncover all numbers.
It is fun for all ages and helps teach addition and subtraction (just don't tell the kids that it is math.) It's a nice alternative to electronic games, and it looks more attractive than a game console too.
2 dice and full instructions are included. The overall dimensions of the box are 11-1/2” x 5-1/4” x 1-3/4”
Finish: Our standard finish of Danish Oil (to bring out the wood's color & grain), followed by several brushed-on coats of semi-gloss polyurethane (to protect the wood's surface).

Product name: 8x10 Paper Printable Cotton Rag Paper Letterpress
Description:
BLANK cotton paper to be used for commercial printing or hand lettering. NEW coordinating papers are offered in a eco-friendly recycled cover/card stock weight.
The cotton rag paper has all natural deckled edges (not torn or cut) and is offered in two weights: 150gsm or 250gsm. The coordinating card stock is made of traditional wood pulp using 100% recycled paper (30% PCW) with smooth surface and cut edges.
This beautiful BLANK handmade paper is made of 100% Cotton Rag using cotton textile remnants. This is NOT mass produced watercolor stock, but instead each piece is handmade on an individual screen. The color of the paper is a natural, unbleached white but may occasionally have tiny speckles of random color from other fibers mixed in the hand making process. All sizes are made from different batches of pulp, so there will be some natural variation in color among the pieces. The photographs with watercolor stain and calligraphy are examples of how this paper can be used.  All papers in my listings, including this one are BLANK.
As a calligrapher who works with a lot of papers, this is premium thick paper with a wonderful feel and tooth to it. All papers have been sized and are perfect for letterpress as well as appropriate for almost any use including pen and ink, drawing, colored or graphite pencils or light washes of watercolors. It will also work for mixed media.  Both weights of the paper will print on the top feed area of my personal inkjet printer using the envelope setting.  However, I cannot guarantee that your printer can handle them and suggest samples or blemished papers be used for any testing.  
The cotton edges are beautiful with a natural deckle NOT hand torn with the exception of the cotton rag envelopes.
These papers are offered as blanks.

Red: Iron Oxide ~ Matte Finish ~ Physical Form: Red Powder (color looks dark)

Brown: Iron Oxides ~ Matte Finish ~ Physical Form: Brown Powder
Green: Chromium Oxide ~ Matte Finish ~ Physical Form: Green Powder

You can use the colors by themselves or to deepen the tone of other colors. This all natural color has been filtered of harmful impurities. When used in clear bases, the color will not remain transparent.
A pastel color is produced in opaque (white) bases.
Solubility: Disperses in Water
Storage: Room temperature. Air tight container.
Product pH: Color will not change in products with a high pH. 
Matte: This color is not light sensitive /  Mica;: The colors are light sensitive
Color Migration: If product design has layered colors, this color will not migrate or “bleed” between layers. 
Non bleeding  / Does not Morph
Cosmetics: Add color directly to your base.
Melt & Pour (MnP) (MP) Soap: Add your color to a small amount of liquid glycerin. Mix well, then add amount desired to melted soap base. The more product you add the
darker your color will be. Some micas will work in cold process soap - but some will not. Their colors are sometimes unstable in the high ph of raw cold processed soap.  Do a small test batch first, or test out a little bit of mica in a little bit of lye water to see if the color shifts in that recipe.  Mica powder can used in an opaque base to make a light or Pastel color, but may have little to no sparkle as light is needed for the true reflective qualities of the micas to work properly.
***NOTE: If your bubbles or lather are not white you have used too much color. A little goes a long way. If you would like a true color, try using a clear soap. 
Do not over use this product.
Be sure to mix well. Speckling sometimes occur in MP (melt & pour).

Gold filled is a great economical alternative to solid gold. Gold filled is not to be confused with gold-plated. Gold filled is a layer of gold bonded to another metal. It has 100% more gold. Jewelry Care
•Please note that proper care and maintenance is required to keep your jewelry beautiful. Jewelry does not like water so please remove before swimming or bathing.
